## Known Issues & Things to Watch

### OkCupid selector drift
OkCupid frequently changes its CSS class names. If `readThreads()` returns 0 threads or `extractCurrentThread()` returns no messages, the selectors in `okcupidAdapter.ts` need updating. The key selectors are in `extractCurrentThread()` — try Chrome DevTools on the messages page to find current class names.

### CDP port conflict
If `npm run chrome:debug` says Chrome is already running on 9222 but the agent still can't connect, Chrome may have been launched without debugging. Quit Chrome entirely and re-run `chrome:debug`.

### Sender detection
Message bubbles need to be identified as "me" vs "match". The current logic checks for `sent`, `outgoing`, `mine`, `self` in the element's class name or data-testid. If messages are all being attributed to the wrong sender, inspect the DOM and update the sender detection logic in `extractCurrentThread()`.

### Claude JSON output
`claudeReplyAgent.ts` strips markdown fences and parses the Claude response as JSON. If Claude starts wrapping its output differently, update the cleaning logic around `JSON.parse`.

